\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces $\beta $-sweep of H-PSMG\textsuperscript  {+}'s type-discrimination bonus on HP-SPGG c19 across four LLM backbones, each labelled at the curve's right endpoint. Three qualitatively distinct regimes appear, each predicted by Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}. \emph  {Extreme self-decay} on GPT-5.4-nano and Kimi-K2.6: regret is essentially flat across all $\beta $ because the type posterior concentrates faster than the bonus has time to drive useful exploration; this is the boundary case of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(i). \emph  {Self-decay edge} on DeepSeek-V3.2: regret stays at $0.40$ for $\beta \leq 0.75$ and rises mildly at higher $\beta $ as the bonus begins to pull the algorithm off welfare-optimal actions, matching the high-$\beta $ boundary regime of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(i). \emph  {Burn-in jump} on Llama-Maverick: regret falls sharply from $0.97$ at $\beta \leq 0.1$ to $0.31$ at $\beta = 0.25$ and stays flat thereafter, the empirical signature of the exponential-in-$|\Theta |^n$ burn-in improvement of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(ii). The shaded vertical band marks the $\beta = 0.1 \to 0.25$ burn-in transition zone where Llama crosses regimes.}}{20}{figure.caption.20}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:beta-sweep}{{2}{20}{$\beta $-sweep of H-PSMG\textsuperscript {+}'s type-discrimination bonus on HP-SPGG c19 across four LLM backbones, each labelled at the curve's right endpoint. Three qualitatively distinct regimes appear, each predicted by Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}. \emph {Extreme self-decay} on GPT-5.4-nano and Kimi-K2.6: regret is essentially flat across all $\beta $ because the type posterior concentrates faster than the bonus has time to drive useful exploration; this is the boundary case of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(i). \emph {Self-decay edge} on DeepSeek-V3.2: regret stays at $0.40$ for $\beta \leq 0.75$ and rises mildly at higher $\beta $ as the bonus begins to pull the algorithm off welfare-optimal actions, matching the high-$\beta $ boundary regime of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(i). \emph {Burn-in jump} on Llama-Maverick: regret falls sharply from $0.97$ at $\beta \leq 0.1$ to $0.31$ at $\beta = 0.25$ and stays flat thereafter, the empirical signature of the exponential-in-$|\Theta |^n$ burn-in improvement of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(ii). The shaded vertical band marks the $\beta = 0.1 \to 0.25$ burn-in transition zone where Llama crosses regimes}{figure.caption.20}{}}
