\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces E1 posterior concentration speed predicts the H-PSMG\textsuperscript  {+} bonus regime. Each marker is one LLM backbone. The horizontal axis is the mean per-seed concentration time $K_{\mathrm  {conc}}^{0.9}$, the first episode at which the H-PSMG ($\beta = 0$) posterior on the true type for all agents exceeds $0.9$. The vertical axis is the empirically observed bonus benefit, $\mathrm  {Reg}(\text  {H-PSMG}) - \mathrm  {Reg}(\text  {H-PSMG}^+)$ at $\beta = 0.25$, positive when the bonus helps. The three background bands correspond to the three regimes of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}. DeepSeek-V3.2 sits in the self-decay edge regime (the bonus self-decays before useful exploration but still produces a gentle positive benefit); Llama-4-Maverick sits in the burn-in jump regime predicted by Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(ii); GPT-5.4-nano and Kimi-K2.6 sit in an intermediate boundary regime where the bonus over-explores at finite $\beta $.}}{22}{figure.caption.24}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:e1-posterior-concentration}{{3}{22}{E1 posterior concentration speed predicts the H-PSMG\textsuperscript {+} bonus regime. Each marker is one LLM backbone. The horizontal axis is the mean per-seed concentration time $K_{\mathrm {conc}}^{0.9}$, the first episode at which the H-PSMG ($\beta = 0$) posterior on the true type for all agents exceeds $0.9$. The vertical axis is the empirically observed bonus benefit, $\mathrm {Reg}(\text {H-PSMG}) - \mathrm {Reg}(\text {H-PSMG}^+)$ at $\beta = 0.25$, positive when the bonus helps. The three background bands correspond to the three regimes of Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}. DeepSeek-V3.2 sits in the self-decay edge regime (the bonus self-decays before useful exploration but still produces a gentle positive benefit); Llama-4-Maverick sits in the burn-in jump regime predicted by Theorem~\ref {thm:hpsmg-plus}(ii); GPT-5.4-nano and Kimi-K2.6 sit in an intermediate boundary regime where the bonus over-explores at finite $\beta $}{figure.caption.24}{}}
